      "description": "Up for sale is a mechanically sound 2003 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S, featuring the iconic wide-body chassis and the M96 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six. This specimen delivers 320 hp and 273 lb-ft of torque through a 6-speed manual transaxle and a viscous-clutch AWD system. It features a documented LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a recently replaced Rear Main Seal (RMS), addressing the primary mechanical concerns of this engine architecture. The VarioCam Plus system provides a linear power band, while the suspension geometry remains tight with upgraded Bilstein B6 dampers. Braking is handled by factory-spec four-piston monoblock calipers over cross-drilled rotors. The interior and exterior show honest wear consistent with a well-maintained driver\u2019s car, but the powertrain and drivetrain are dialed in for high-performance use. DME overrev report available upon request.",
